## Summary

The meeting will be held on the 7--9th July 2025 at the University of Oxford, United Kingdom.

The format will be similar to earlier Basilisk/Gerris meetings held in [Paris, France in 2011](http://gfs.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Gerris_users%27_meeting_2011), [Wellington, New Zealand in 2012](http://gfs.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Gerris_users%27_meeting_2012), [Sevilla, Spain in 2014](http://gfs.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Meeting_on_Numerical_challenges_in_two-phase_flows), [Princeton, USA in 2017](BGUM2017), [Paris, France in 2019](BGUM2019) and [Paris, France in 2023](BGUM2023). Participants are encouraged to share their work using Basilisk (or Gerris) for applications in fluid mechanics, environmental science, engineering etc. Students are especially welcome to participate in this informal and friendly gathering.

Attendance is free of charge but registration is mandatory.

## Participants

To register simply [edit this page](/_edit/BGUM2025) using either your own Basilisk login or login *guest*, password *bgum2025* and add yourself to the list below. If you intend to give a talk please give a tentative title. Talk slots are usually 20 minutes, depending on the number of participants. Note that the number of participants will be limited to 100, on a first-registered / first-served basis, so please register early!

